description: Retrieves information about one or more custom data identifiers.

nested_items.name: customDataIdentifiers
nested_items.description: An array of objects, one for each custom data identifier that matches the criteria specified in the request.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the custom data identifier.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The date and time, in UTC and extended ISO 8601 format, when the custom data identifier was created.

nested_items.name: deleted
nested_items.description: Specifies whether the custom data identifier was deleted. If you delete a custom data identifier, Amazon Macie doesn't delete it permanently. Instead, it soft deletes the identifier.

nested_items.name: description
nested_items.description: The custom description of the custom data identifier.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The unique identifier for the custom data identifier.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The custom name of the custom data identifier.

nested_items.name: notFoundIdentifierIds
nested_items.description: An array of custom data identifier IDs, one for each custom data identifier that was specified in the request but doesn't correlate to an existing custom data identifier.
